  "quest.030CB1D21EF1ACEB.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from diamond hammer (see JEI for exact mats).",
    "",
    "Top-tier manual hammer — maximum durability for endless crushing sessions.",
  ],
  "quest.0390C6E1DFB89260.quest_desc": [
    "Cook silkworms in a furnace, smoker, or campfire for emergency food while you build better farms.",
    "",
    "Not glamorous, but skyblock hunger is real when you are busy sieving. Keep a few cooked silkworms as trail food between random-block mining sessions.",
  ],
  "quest.04885FC3F762FA35.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of end stone in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed end stone from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.04E39C1E315761B7.quest_desc": [
    "Thorium ore chunks drop when you sieve end stone, crushed end stone, and compressed end stone with at least a diamond mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add end stone blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Thorium in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.055224309CBABB1E.quest_desc": [
    "Craft an oak crucible to melt items and fluids in skyblock — cobble to lava, ice to water, and other heat recipes (see JEI crucible heat sources).",
    "",
    "Place a heat source underneath (torch, fire, magma, etc. per recipe). Crucibles bridge the gap when random block has not given you lava yet.",
    "",
    "Porcelain crucibles are a later upgrade for higher-tier fluids; oak is your starter.",
  ],
  "quest.0A19396D2C5933FA.quest_desc": [
    "Requires flint mesh in the upgrade recipe (check JEI).",
    "",
    "Upgrade from flint mesh with iron. Iron mesh is the workhorse tier: most common ore chunks (iron, copper, tin, nickel, aluminum, lead, zinc, osmium) start appearing when you sieve stone, gravel, sand, and deepslate.",
    "",
    "Meshes are not consumed — swap them in the sieve UI when you upgrade tiers.",
  ],
  "quest.0AD067CE4FA05CB0.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from golden watering can in a crafting table.",
    "",
    "High-tier farming tool before netherite. Use on infested-leaves silk farms and large platforms.",
  ],
  "quest.0BDF7FBBB23F5A75.quest_desc": [
    "Lithium ore chunks drop when you sieve deepslate and cobbled deepslate with at least a golden mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add deepslate blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Lithium in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.0C7B0803E6729957.quest_desc": [
    "The compressed sieve processes entire compressed blocks (compressed gravel, sand, dust, etc.) in one operation — far faster than sieving nine singles.",
    "",
    "Requires an oak sieve in the dependency chain: you should already know manual sieving before bulk processing.",
    "",
    "Feed it compressed materials from your random block and from the compression quests in this chapter. Match mesh tier to the ore chunks you need (iron mesh minimum for most metals).",
  ],
  "quest.0CAD460EE0859F73.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of soul sand in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed soul sand from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.0EB3542B8101E102.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from wooden hammer (see JEI for exact mats).",
    "",
    "Craft from stone and sticks. Faster crushing with more durability than wood. Use on compressed cobble, deepslate, blackstone, and other stone compressed blocks.",
  ],
  "quest.128BF56BDD8A8031.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of moss block in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed moss block from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.14A245109B2568D7.quest_desc": [
    "Use a hammer on compressed deepslate (right-click the block in the world or use the Ex Deorum crushing recipe) to create crushed variants. Crushed blocks are the intermediate step between compressed stone and fine dust or sieve inputs.",
    "",
    "Crushed materials sieve into pebbles and ore chunks at higher mesh tiers. Hammer tier affects speed — upgrade hammers as your random block supplies more stone.",
    "",
    "You can also compress 9 crushed blocks into a compressed crushed block for storage (see related quests in this row).",
  ],
  "quest.17F21A2014021233.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of diorite in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed diorite from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.18199AC996F8FE2F.quest_desc": [
    "Use a hammer on compressed end stone (right-click the block in the world or use the Ex Deorum crushing recipe) to create crushed variants. Crushed blocks are the intermediate step between compressed stone and fine dust or sieve inputs.",
    "",
    "Crushed materials sieve into pebbles and ore chunks at higher mesh tiers. Hammer tier affects speed — upgrade hammers as your random block supplies more stone.",
    "",
    "You can also compress 9 crushed blocks into a compressed crushed block for storage (see related quests in this row).",
  ],
  "quest.18823AE1287C443E.quest_desc": [
    "Compress 9 crushed end stone in a crafting grid for bulk storage. These blocks let you stockpile entire hammer output without filling dozens of chest slots.",
    "",
    "Decompress or hammer them back down when you need crushed material for sieving. JEI shows both directions.",
    "",
    "Random block loot may drop these directly once Ex Deorum is unlocked — grab them when you see them.",
  ],
  "quest.1926DA8208B275AE.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from copper watering can in a crafting table.",
    "",
    "Reliable workhorse for moss, trees, and crop patches fed by random block drops.",
  ],
  "quest.1C1AE2C77CD283A8.quest_desc": [
    "Hold and right-click crops, saplings, and grass. Watering cans speed up growth and are required for some barrel and garden recipes. Refill in water.",
  ],
  "quest.1CE84112AA105327.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from diamond watering can in a crafting table.",
    "",
    "Best watering can in Ex Deorum. One refill goes a long way when expanding your island canopy.",
  ],
  "quest.1E3690A44FB6BE66.quest_desc": [
    "Iron ore chunks drop when you sieve gravel, sand, deepslate, netherrack, and other stone types with at least an iron mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add stone-family blocks blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Iron in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.21FC2BAED300401F.quest_desc": [
    "Craft an oak barrel — the composting and fluid workstation of Ex Deorum. Add organic items (saplings, crops, silkworms, leaves) to make dirt, clay, witch water, and other skyblock staples over time.",
    "",
    "Barrels also handle fluid mixing and transformations (water + lava = cobble, etc. depending on recipe). Check JEI under Ex Deorum barrel categories.",
    "",
    "Place barrels near your crook/infested-leaves farm so compost inputs are one hop away.",
  ],
  "quest.22A3ABB7F7F920C0.quest_desc": [
    "Dust is the fine product of sieving sand and gravel (flint mesh and better) or decompressing compressed dust. It is used in porcelain recipes, barrel mixing, and some mod integrations.",
    "",
    "Set up a sieve over a hopper or place dust manually. Pair gravel and sand from your random block with a flint or iron mesh to start a steady dust income.",
    "",
    "Compressed dust stores 9× dust — craft it when dust stacks clog your inventory.",
  ],
  "quest.22DD9AA87FF627F3.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of deepslate in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed deepslate from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.22E9A734075BE72C.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from compressed wooden hammer.",
    "",
    "Stone-tier compressed hammer. Uses compressed materials in its recipe — craft when you have steady compressed cobble from mining or compressing.",
    "",
    "Compressed hammers use compressed cobble (or higher) in recipes — align this quest with your compressed cobblestone stock.",
  ],
  "quest.23201C6F37CBF8CB.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from wooden hammer.",
    "",
    "A wooden hammer built with compressed cobble in the recipe. Crushes entire stacks more efficiently and is the gateway to the compressed hammer upgrade line.",
    "",
    "Compressed hammers use compressed cobble (or higher) in recipes — align this quest with your compressed cobblestone stock.",
  ],
  "quest.2450BA60D0896E03.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of red sand in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed red sand from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.25E04CACAD8D2D2E.quest_desc": [
    "Copper ore chunks drop when you sieve cobble, granite, diorite, andesite, or gravel piles with at least an iron mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add stone and gravel blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Copper in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.2618BFD7249F2BB8.quest_desc": [
    "Bone crook is a sturdier variant crafted with bones. Same function as a normal crook on infested leaves, but better for long farming sessions.",
    "",
    "Use whichever crook you have when breaking infested leaves for silkworms. Bones often appear from random mob loot or kitchen mods later.",
  ],
  "quest.299D7BE7048102C9.quest_desc": [
    "Boron ore chunks drop when you sieve sand, clay balls from barrels, and gravel with at least an iron mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add clay and sand blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Boron in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.2D75FB5FB9D83374.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from compressed iron hammer.",
    "",
    "Golden compressed hammer — faster swings, great for processing loot between sieve cycles.",
    "",
    "Compressed hammers use compressed cobble (or higher) in recipes — align this quest with your compressed cobblestone stock.",
  ],
  "quest.2E6616B12F8684D7.quest_desc": [
