    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.31E78B7BFE91D9E2.quest_desc": [
    "Cobalt ore chunks drop when you sieve blackstone, basalt, and netherrack with at least a diamond mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add nether stone blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Cobalt in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.32A620B46D18E41D.quest_desc": [
    "Compress 9 crushed netherrack in a crafting grid for bulk storage. These blocks let you stockpile entire hammer output without filling dozens of chest slots.",
    "",
    "Decompress or hammer them back down when you need crushed material for sieving. JEI shows both directions.",
    "",
    "Random block loot may drop these directly once Ex Deorum is unlocked — grab them when you see them.",
  ],
  "quest.37CFE7B7327C9F02.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of cobblestone in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
