    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.380BC2D282E35D07.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of granite in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed granite from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.383BDDD954633572.quest_desc": [
    "Magnesium ore chunks drop when you sieve gravel, diorite, and limestone-like pebbles with at least an iron mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add gravel and stone blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Magnesium in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.3AB3DC16A7BAA3BD.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from stone watering can in a crafting table.",
    "",
    "Copper-tier can — better durability for daily farming on a small island.",
  ],
  "quest.3BFA03189D833994.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from compressed diamond hammer.",
    "",
    "The ultimate manual crushing tool. Build when you are ready to automate ore chunk production at scale.",
    "",
    "Compressed hammers use compressed cobble (or higher) in recipes — align this quest with your compressed cobblestone stock.",
  ],
  "quest.3C110226142BBC3D.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of cobbled deepslate in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed cobbled deepslate from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.3C158388E46634EB.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from iron watering can in a crafting table.",
    "",
    "Premium growth boost for players running multiple sapling lines from sieve loot.",
  ],
  "quest.3CD0599A267DE091.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from iron hammer (see JEI for exact mats).",
    "",
    "High-speed crushing for players who sieve a lot of gravel and stone. Golden hammers trade some durability for faster processing.",
  ],
  "quest.3D35A5E8C9D4C211.quest_desc": [
    "Lead ore chunks drop when you sieve gravel, basalt pebbles, and stone variants with at least an iron mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add gravel and stone blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Lead in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.3D7DEFB8E2F66B57.quest_desc": [
    "Requires string mesh in the upgrade recipe (check JEI).",
    "",
    "Upgrade from string mesh using flint. Flint mesh unlocks pebbles from gravel, flint from gravel, and early dust lines — the first real step toward ore chunks.",
    "",
    "Meshes are not consumed — swap them in the sieve UI when you upgrade tiers.",
  ],
  "quest.3E3A0D8F8C2F93DC.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of gravel in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed gravel from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.4101B3D526BA095C.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from wooden watering can in a crafting table.",
    "",
    "Upgraded capacity and reach. Upgrade when you start tree farms and barrel compost lines.",
  ],
  "quest.43061CE98D8F779A.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a crook from sticks. Right-click infested leaves (from random block or silkworm farming) to break them faster and boost silkworm drops.",
    "",
    "Infested leaves are how Ex Deorum skyblock gets string and silk without exploring. The crook is cheap — make one early and keep it in your hotbar next to your hammer.",
  ],
  "quest.46CB48C7B9058439.quest_desc": [
    "Compress 9 crushed deepslate in a crafting grid for bulk storage. These blocks let you stockpile entire hammer output without filling dozens of chest slots.",
    "",
    "Decompress or hammer them back down when you need crushed material for sieving. JEI shows both directions.",
    "",
    "Random block loot may drop these directly once Ex Deorum is unlocked — grab them when you see them.",
  ],
  "quest.47C6AE0A4331C237.quest_desc": [
    "Osmium ore chunks drop when you sieve cobble, deepslate, and andesite with at least an iron mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add stone variants blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Osmium in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.4897B1997578A52F.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from stone hammer (see JEI for exact mats).",
    "",
    "Mid-game hammer with solid durability. Essential once you are crushing large stacks of compressed stone from your random block loot.",
  ],
  "quest.4959DAC0E8D7F0C5.quest_desc": [
    "Tin ore chunks drop when you sieve gravel, sand, and some stone pebbles with at least an iron mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add gravel and sand blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Tin in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.4A904E2EF22F6D51.quest_desc": [
    "Craft the entry-level mesh from string. Place it in a sieve (oak sieve to start). String mesh handles gentle drops: saplings, seeds, dirt pieces, and other light materials from composted barrels.",
    "",
    "Meshes are not consumed — swap them in the sieve UI when you upgrade tiers.",
  ],
  "quest.4ACF2F8593A2246D.quest_desc": [
    "Obtain silkworms from breaking infested leaves with a crook. Silkworms are composted in barrels, cooked for food, or used in recipes that need organic bulk.",
    "",
    "Farm loop: infested leaves (random block) → crook → silkworms → barrel compost → dirt/clay/water products. String mesh also comes from string, so this line feeds your first sieve tier.",
  ],
  "quest.4BB05FAF3A10EABB.quest_desc": [
    "Craft an oak sieve — your first sieving station. Insert a mesh (start with string mesh), add gravel, sand, dirt, or stone blocks, and collect drops from the output.",
    "",
    "Manual sieving is how you turn random-block cobble and gravel into ore chunks. Stand something beneath it or pick up drops quickly on a small island.",
    "",
    "Upgrade to oak compressed sieve when you process full stacks of compressed gravel or sand.",
  ],
  "quest.4BEFED9458AF745F.quest_desc": [
    "Nickel ore chunks drop when you sieve deepslate, cobbled deepslate, and stone with at least an iron mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add deepslate and stone blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Nickel in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.4C77D9E66CDDD49D.quest_desc": [
    "Silver ore chunks drop when you sieve sand, gravel, and soul sand with at least a golden mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add sand and gravel blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Silver in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.4F2AD810A4A8FEEA.quest_desc": [
    "Your first hammer for Ex Deorum processing. Right-click compressed blocks to crush them into gravel, sand, or crushed stone variants. Hammers consume durability — keep a backup while learning the rhythm.",
  ],
  "quest.4FCD17EEBFDBE328.quest_desc": [
    "Requires iron mesh in the upgrade recipe (check JEI).",
    "",
    "Upgrade from iron mesh with gold. Golden mesh improves drop rates and unlocks precious metals (gold, silver, lithium) and better yields on sand and gravel.",
    "",
    "Meshes are not consumed — swap them in the sieve UI when you upgrade tiers.",
  ],
  "quest.507B1C35EC4E4D3E.quest_desc": [
    "Platinum ore chunks drop when you sieve blackstone and crushed blackstone with at least a diamond mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add blackstone blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Platinum in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.5B784C734CBA7999.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of netherrack in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed netherrack from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.616F0248BBC73583.quest_desc": [
    "Zinc ore chunks drop when you sieve gravel and granite pebbles with at least an iron mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add gravel blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Zinc in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.62104B5BD6545B9F.quest_desc": [
    "Requires diamond mesh in the upgrade recipe (check JEI).",
    "",
    "The top sieve tier. Upgrade from diamond mesh with netherite. Use this for the rarest ore chunks (iridium) and the best conversion rates on compressed sieves.",
    "",
    "Meshes are not consumed — swap them in the sieve UI when you upgrade tiers.",
  ],
  "quest.648BFAFA30863498.quest_desc": [
    "Uranium ore chunks drop when you sieve deepslate and compressed deepslate with at least a diamond mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add deepslate blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Uranium in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.66933F94FDF704AB.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from golden hammer (see JEI for exact mats).",
    "",
    "Late-game hammer for bulk crushing before compressing again. Pairs well with mechanical hammer automation later.",
  ],
  "quest.6832EF8F46B42D52.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of sand in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed sand from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.689F2DFDC6B8D472.quest_desc": [
    "Gold ore chunks drop when you sieve sand, gravel, and nether gravel variants with at least a golden mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add sand and gravel blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Gold in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.69B1D4E0AB31BD5F.quest_desc": [
    "The mechanical hammer automates crushing compressed blocks. Place it, supply compressed stone (or configured inputs), and let it output crushed/gravel products without wearing out manual hammers.",
    "",
    "Power it per your pack's Ex Deorum version (check JEI for this NeoForge build). Pair with chests or pipes from storage mods when you unlock them.",
    "",
    "This is the bridge between manual skyblock grinding and real automation — worth building once your random block feeds compressed cobble steadily.",
  ],
  "quest.6A90824B453CDFC7.quest_desc": [
    "Requires golden mesh in the upgrade recipe (check JEI).",
    "",
    "Upgrade from golden mesh with diamonds. Diamond mesh targets late overworld and nether materials: uranium, thorium, platinum, cobalt, and high-tier pebbles.",
    "",
    "Meshes are not consumed — swap them in the sieve UI when you upgrade tiers.",
  ],
  "quest.6C883C1773842248.quest_desc": [
    "Iridium ore chunks drop when you sieve netherrack, crushed netherrack, and nether gravel with at least a netherite mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add nether materials blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Iridium in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.6D76BB73E64B6C5F.quest_desc": [
    "Use a hammer on compressed blackstone (right-click the block in the world or use the Ex Deorum crushing recipe) to create crushed variants. Crushed blocks are the intermediate step between compressed stone and fine dust or sieve inputs.",
    "",
    "Crushed materials sieve into pebbles and ore chunks at higher mesh tiers. Hammer tier affects speed — upgrade hammers as your random block supplies more stone.",
    "",
    "You can also compress 9 crushed blocks into a compressed crushed block for storage (see related quests in this row).",
  ],
  "quest.712B09669EA85DB7.quest_desc": [
    "Use a hammer on compressed netherrack (right-click the block in the world or use the Ex Deorum crushing recipe) to create crushed variants. Crushed blocks are the intermediate step between compressed stone and fine dust or sieve inputs.",
    "",
    "Crushed materials sieve into pebbles and ore chunks at higher mesh tiers. Hammer tier affects speed — upgrade hammers as your random block supplies more stone.",
    "",
    "You can also compress 9 crushed blocks into a compressed crushed block for storage (see related quests in this row).",
  ],
  "quest.7360394B1A918F1E.quest_desc": [
    "Aluminum ore chunks drop when you sieve gravel and compressed gravel with at least an iron mesh (higher tiers improve rates).",
    "",
    "Place an oak sieve (or better), insert the mesh, and add gravel blocks from your random one-block loot. Click or automate with a mechanical sieve later.",
    "",
    "Ore chunks are how Ex Deorum replaces mining Aluminum in skyblock — stockpile them until you unlock proper ore processing mods in the pack.",
  ],
  "quest.74751F0BFBCAF7B4.quest_desc": [
    "Automates sieving: insert mesh, feed gravel/sand/stone, collect ore chunks and byproducts automatically.",
    "",
    "Runs slower per tick than a diligent player with a diamond mesh, but it runs while you mine the center block. Hook up item storage when you can.",
    "",
    "Use the same mesh tier rules as manual sieves — upgrade meshes in the block UI as your ore needs advance.",
  ],
  "quest.761A5CFA7AD75428.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from compressed stone hammer.",
    "",
    "Iron-tier compressed hammer for heavy skyblock sessions. Ideal when your random block feeds you full stacks of compressed stone.",
    "",
    "Compressed hammers use compressed cobble (or higher) in recipes — align this quest with your compressed cobblestone stock.",
  ],
  "quest.7C30B3A03714AEC1.quest_desc": [
    "Craft a 3×3 square of andesite in a crafting table to make one compressed block. Compressed blocks store 9× the material in one inventory slot — critical on a one-block skyblock where random loot fills your pockets fast.",
    "",
    "Mine compressed andesite from your random block pool (after the Ex Deorum unlock), or compress what you already have. You can place the block for building or hammer/crush it in later quests for sieving and ore processing.",
    "",
    "Tip: keep at least one compressed stack of each material type as feedstock for hammers, sieves, and decompress recipes in JEI.",
  ],
  "quest.7F960CE8D9FCC08D.quest_desc": [
    "Upgrade from compressed golden hammer.",
    "",
    "Diamond-tier compressed hammer. Use before or alongside the mechanical hammer to crush bulk compressed blocks.",
    "",
    "Compressed hammers use compressed cobble (or higher) in recipes — align this quest with your compressed cobblestone stock.",
  ],
  "quest.7FF9305C2B04B7C5.quest_desc": [
    "Compress 9 crushed blackstone in a crafting grid for bulk storage. These blocks let you stockpile entire hammer output without filling dozens of chest slots.",
    "",
    "Decompress or hammer them back down when you need crushed material for sieving. JEI shows both directions.",
    "",
    "Random block loot may drop these directly once Ex Deorum is unlocked — grab them when you see them.",
  ],
